text: Have been eating this kway chap for years. In terms of quality and value its 4 out of 5. In times of high living cost, they are still trying to maintain a set meal at $5.80 is not easy. My meal with an additional soft and fresh bowl of kway cost a total of $6.80 which can satisfy 2 small eater. For single big eater, this is very satisfying until i need to take 5 mins of rest before leaving. I would recommend this stall and their other menu available. They operate long hours from morning till 9pm.

I wouldn't say I dislike this, so it wouldn't deserve anything less than 2 stars. Yet it's really not that fantastic, but it helped to satisfy a craving for Kway Chup/Chap... The bowl of Kway Chup was bigger than expected nevertheless, though it cost more in the first place than other of such stalls which offer Kway Chup in smaller bowls...

Unfortunately, this is the only kway chap option within the vicinity that I live. Fortunately however, it wasn't bad but rather acceptable and priced reasonably. Only few choices though. I liked the small intestine most. You can also add a bowl of kidney soup at extra cost ❤️
Having this stall many years taste good.
Tasteless peanuts n chili sauce is bitter. At first I thought my intestines  are not cleaned enough when I tasted bitter.
